    "2026-06-30 V5c — Descriptions (`///`) (paired with V5c-T): fills src/parser/descriptions.ts. joinDocComment joins the `///` RestOfLine contents with \\n and strips the common leading whitespace of the non-blank lines (same algorithm as the query-template dedent QRY-7: common prefix drawn from {U+0020 space, U+0009 tab}; whitespace-only lines ignored for the common-prefix walk and normalised to an empty line). extractDescription walks the comment lines from the end, collecting the maximal trailing run of `///` lines via ^[ \\t]*///(?!/)(.*)$ (the negative lookahead keeps a four-slash //// line out of the doc-comment run), so a regular // line terminates the run and is not propagated and a block with no `///` line yields undefined; the captured RestOfLine contents are passed to joinDocComment. lowerDescription writes the joined text byte-for-byte into description: for the schema/enum/field/variant anchors (pre-existing fragment keys preserved via spread) and returns the fragment unchanged for fn (functions have no JSON Schema — the description stays AST-only). checkDocCommentPlacement fires loom/parse/doc-comment-misplaced (\"'///' doc comment is not legal above this production\", severity error, located at the site) for any production outside the eligible set {schema, enum, field, variant, fn} and undefined for an eligible anchor. Message anchored to code-registry-parse.md per the Diagnostic message anchors rule. Pure functions — no module-level state, no broad catch, no ambient primitive, no Promise combinator, no Sync call. All 4 V5c-T tests green; full suite 251 green, typecheck + lint clean.",
    "2026-06-30 V5c-T — Descriptions (`///`) tests (paired V5c impl): the src/parser/descriptions.ts seam (joinDocComment(docLines) / extractDescription(commentLines) / lowerDescription(text, anchor, fragment) / checkDocCommentPlacement(production, site), inert stubs; DocCommentSite / DocAnchorKind = \"schema\"|\"enum\"|\"field\"|\"variant\"|\"fn\" shapes) plus tests/descriptions.test.ts with 4 failing tests pinning descriptions.md + grammar.md §`///` placement. §No transformation / §Placement: lowerDescription writes the joined text byte-for-byte into description: for the schema/enum/field/variant anchors (pre-existing fragment keys preserved), while a fn anchor lowers nowhere — the `///` is preserved AST-only and the lowered fragment carries no description. §Placement / grammar.md §`///` placement: loom/parse/doc-comment-misplaced (\"'///' doc comment is not legal above this production\") fires above let/import/export/expression/control-flow productions and raises none above the five eligible anchors (schema/enum/field/variant/fn). §Multi-line: joinDocComment joins consecutive `///` RestOfLine contents with \\n, strips the common leading whitespace of non-blank lines (same algorithm as query-template dedent), and turns an empty `///` line into a blank line (\"   first line\", \"\", \"   second line\" → \"first line\\n\\nsecond line\"; single line strips its one-space prefix). §`//` is a regular code comment: extractDescription collects only the trailing `///` run, so a leading `//` line is not propagated ([\"// noise\",\"/// line one\",\"/// line two\"] → \"line one\\nline two\"; a block with no `///` line → undefined). Message anchored to code-registry-parse.md per the Diagnostic message anchors rule. Typecheck + lint clean; the 4 tests red on their own primary assertions (absent description / absent diagnostic / empty join) because the V5c lowering is absent — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason; the other 247 tests stay green.",
    "2026-06-30 V5b — Discriminated unions, recursion, and cycle detection (paired with V5b-T): implements the three V5b seams on src/parser/schema-declarations.ts. checkDiscriminatedUnion dispatches on the explicit `by` field; implicit detection runs on the wire name (wireName ?? name) across the variants — evaluateField classifies each candidate wire-name as present-in-all, all-literal, all-string, value-unique. A present-in-all single-string-literal unique-value field qualifies; exactly one qualifier is the discriminator (no diagnostic); two or more fire loom/parse/ambiguous-discriminator (qualifying names in first-seen source order, comma-space joined); zero qualifiers resolve in precedence order — a string-shaped field with duplicate values fires loom/parse/duplicate-discriminator-value, else a present-in-all single-literal non-string field fires loom/parse/non-string-discriminator (\"got <kind>\"), else loom/parse/missing-discriminator. The explicit by-field path checks nested-value first (loom/parse/nested-discriminator, since a nested value's type/value cannot be read), then non-string literal (loom/parse/non-string-discriminator, the constraint applying equally to the explicit form), then duplicate value (loom/parse/duplicate-discriminator-value). checkByClause fires loom/parse/by-on-object-schema for the object body and undefined for the union form. detectTypeAliasCycles runs a recursion-stack DFS over the resolved reference graph (after schema-name resolution, before lowering): a back-edge to an on-stack node whose cycle slice is all-alias fires loom/parse/type-alias-cycle with the path joined by \" → \" and deduped per sorted node-set; a cycle traversing at least one object-schema hop crosses a $ref against $defs and raises nothing; dangling references are ignored. Parse-time literal values rendered bare-when-identifier-shaped else double-quoted per placeholder-rendering-b.md category 5. Pure functions — no module-level state, no broad catch, no ambient primitive, no Promise combinator, no Sync call. All 7 V5b-T tests green; full suite 247 green, typecheck + lint clean.",
    "2026-06-30 V5b-T — Discriminated-union / recursion / cycle-detection tests (paired V5b impl): three inert seam stubs on src/parser/schema-declarations.ts (checkDiscriminatedUnion(decl, site) with DiscriminatedUnionDecl / UnionVariantSchema / DiscriminatorCandidateField carrying per-variant literal kind+text and a nested flag and an optional explicit `by` field; checkByClause(decl, site) with ByClauseDecl form object/union; detectTypeAliasCycles(nodes, site) with SchemaGraphNode kind alias/object and references) plus tests/disc-unions-recursion.test.ts with 7 failing tests pinning schemas.md §Discriminated unions + §Recursion. §Discriminated unions: loom/parse/non-string-discriminator (integer kind → \"discriminator 'kind' on Animal must be a string-literal type; got integer\"), loom/parse/ambiguous-discriminator (kind+species both qualify → \"ambiguous discriminator for Animal; candidates: kind, species. Declare explicitly with 'by <field>'.\"), loom/parse/missing-discriminator (no shared single-literal field → \"Animal is a union of object schemas with no shared single-literal discriminator field. Add a 'kind' (or similar) field to each variant, or declare explicitly with 'by <field>'.\"), loom/parse/duplicate-discriminator-value (explicit by kind, both kind: \"same\" → \"duplicate discriminator value 'same' across variants of Animal\"), loom/parse/nested-discriminator (kind: { type: \"x\" } → \"discriminator field 'kind' must be at the top level of each variant of Animal\"), loom/parse/by-on-object-schema (schema X by f { ... } → \"the 'by' clause applies only to discriminated-union schemas (schema X by f = A | B | …)\"; the union form raises none). §Recursion: loom/parse/type-alias-cycle (pure-alias cycle schema X = Y; schema Y = X → \"type-alias cycle: X → Y → X\"; a cycle through an object-schema hop schema Y { f: X } raises none). Messages anchored to code-registry-parse.md per the Diagnostic message anchors rule. Typecheck + lint clean; the 7 tests red on their own primary assertions (an absent expected diagnostic) because the V5b discriminated-union / cycle checker is absent — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason; the other 240 tests stay green.",
    "2026-06-30 V5a — Schema declarations (object / alias / enum) (paired with V5a-T): fills src/parser/schema-declarations.ts. checkObjectSchema fires loom/parse/empty-schema-body for a no-field schema (returns immediately); loom/parse/redundant-wire-name (W) when a field's wire name equals its loom-side name; and loom/parse/wire-name-collision when two fields share an effective wire name (wireName ?? loomName) or an explicit wire name equals another field's loom-side name, each colliding name reported once in source order. checkEnumDeclaration enforces the schemas.md §Enum declarations name-before-value ordering: loom/parse/empty-enum-body for a no-variant enum; loom/parse/duplicate-enum-variant-name for a repeated identifier (so enum X { Low = \"a\", Low = \"b\" } fires the name code, not the value code); loom/parse/non-string-enum-value for an explicit value whose kind is not string (\"got <kind>\"); loom/parse/duplicate-enum-value only when two or more DISTINCT variant names share one explicit string value (enum X { Low = \"x\", High = \"x\" }), grouped via a value→distinct-name-set map so a same-name same-value pair does not also fire the value code. checkInlineEnumForm matches a leading enum[ form and fires loom/parse/inline-enum. checkVariantAccess fires loom/parse/unknown-variant when the variant is absent from knownVariants. Messages anchored to code-registry-parse.md per the Diagnostic message anchors rule. Pure functions — no module-level state, no broad catch, no ambient primitive, no Promise combinator, no Sync call. All 10 V5a-T tests green; full suite 240 green, typecheck + lint clean."
